hopobject.body: I'm sorry, I didn't catch your name precio del glucovance Comparing these figures with the 2009 household spending report, it appears that consumers age 65 and older have been spending less on insurance. Overall household spending by this group was $37,562 in 2009, and it increased more than $1,600 a year by 2011. Total spending on insurance, however, was higher in 2009 at nearly $4,900, and thus fell by about $150 from 2009 to 2011. Health insurance spending rose a bit during this period, so the declines came in other types of insurance.
